stay on the board.

44:13.733 --> 44:16.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I want to know what it really
means that he's taking a leave.

44:16.200 --> 44:20.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is he actually going to be
able to step back and let
somebody else run the company?

44:20.000 --> 44:23.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, so, what
are the core - - what is the
core problem at Uber that comes

44:23.733 --> 44:28.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
through the reporting up to
this point and what we know
from the Holder report that's

44:29.333 --> 44:31.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
just come out?

44:31.366 --> 44:34.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JESSI HEMPEL: I would point to
two problems that are really
highlighted by the Holder

44:35.266 --> 44:36.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
report.

44:36.633 --> 44:38.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The first and the most
egregious is a cultural problem.

44:38.633 --> 44:40.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It starts at the top.

44:40.733 --> 44:44.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a company that has for
too long taken it for granted
that people are disposable,

44:44.533 --> 44:48.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and that the CEO's machismo
attitude has just trickled down.

44:48.900 --> 44:53.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, secondarily, this
is a 14,000-per company,
and Travis has been
running it as if it were

44:54.766 --> 44:56.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
an eight-person start-up.

44:56.933 --> 45:00.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, it has none of the
structures that most
companies put in place
the catch some of this

45:00.300 --> 45:02.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
stuff a lot earlier on.

45:02.166 --> 45:04.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what you really
see in the Holder report.

45:04.300 --> 45:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Holder reports asks for what
at many companies this size are
very basic things, like a better

45:10.933 --> 45:14.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
H.R. structure that works, or a
head of diversity and inclusion
that actually does that job.

45:15.600 --> 45:17.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
These are pretty basic things.

45:17.700 --> 45:21.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, there is
always a question, of course,
when you have a company that's

45:21.066 --> 45:26.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
really built and
around the image of one
person, how much can you
separate that person from

45:27.600 --> 45:31.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the company and how much
the company can thrive
now going forward.

45:31.100 --> 45:35.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JESSI HEMPEL: I mean,
I think that really is
the question for Uber.

45:35.700 --> 45:37.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a paradox of sorts.

45:37.800 --> 45:42.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The reason why Uber has been
so successful so far is also
the reason why the culture

45:42.000 --> 45:44.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is in such crisis.

45:44.100 --> 45:48.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you truly are able to strip
Travis, not just Travis, but
his values from this company,

45:49.133 --> 45:50.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
what do you have left?

45:50.433 --> 45:52.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What are you going
to rebuild it as?

45:52.000 --> 45:54.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What is the vision
going forward?

45:54.066 --> 45:58.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, do you
see any new steps in what you
have seen so far to ensure the

46:00.233 --> 46:04.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
diversity, the better kind of
leadership, the taking away
the bias that's been there?

46:05.700 --> 46:07.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JESSI HEMPEL: Well, absolutely.

46:07.166 --> 46:10.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, this is a company that's
truly taking this seriously.

46:10.233 --> 46:12.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Now, it's about time.

46:12.300 --> 46:17.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But last week, we saw that
the company hired Frances Frei
from Harvard Business School.

46:18.400 --> 46:21.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She's a renowned executive
leadership expert.

46:21.000 --> 46:26.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she's going to come in, and
she says she has full leeway
to do whatever she needs to

46:26.866 --> 46:29.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
do to improve the culture.

46:29.400 --> 46:32.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, you know, the
biggest challenge for
this company right now is
that it has no leadership.

46:34.400 --> 46:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, it's not just that
it doesn't have Travis.

46:35.900 --> 46:38.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's executive ranks are
incredibly thin right now.

46:38.700 --> 46:43.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so Uber's first -- the
first thing it needs to do is
simply put new leaders in place.

46:45.633 --> 46:48.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, frankly, it's a pretty
hard place to recruit
skilled leaders right now.

46:48.033 --> 46:50.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know a heck of a lot
of people who want to go.

46:50.433 --> 46:51.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

46:51.433 --> 46:52.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Excuse me.

46:52.433 --> 46:54.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JESSI HEMPEL: Yes.

46:54.466 --> 46:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: How much impact
has all this had on ridership
and on the bottom line?

46:56.300 --> 46:59.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JESSI HEMPEL: Well, it's
hard to say right now.

46:59.566 --> 47:04.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
