revenues continue to
agree at this company,
and its loss last quarter

47:05.166 --> 47:07.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
shrunk some.

47:07.266 --> 47:10.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we have also seen the
competitor Lyft gain some
market share in the U.S.

47:10.766 --> 47:15.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I have heard that
advertisers are a little
nervous about putting
their brand next to

47:16.366 --> 47:18.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Uber right now.

47:18.400 --> 47:20.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I think that we're
going to start to see over the
long term, over the next few

47:20.933 --> 47:23.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
