added about 840,000 jobs.

49:55.100 --> 49:59.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
In the four months since
his inauguration, it's
added about 600,000.

49:59.133 --> 50:01.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
STEVEN RATTNER: The U.S. economy
is like a huge battleship.

50:01.900 --> 50:03.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It doesn't turn fast.

50:03.966 --> 50:08.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I think to judge any
president by a few months of
results, whether they're good

50:09.666 --> 50:11.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
or bad, is way premature.

50:11.733 --> 50:16.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Veronique de
Rugy, a libertarian economist
at George Mason University, says

50:18.100 --> 50:20.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
